caption: I stayed at the courtyard and was looking for a breakfast place without breaking the bank, but at the same time I wanted to get out of the "subway" and type of confort zone. This place is very nice and inexpensive. The food was very good. They serve omelets,  scrambled eggs, and many other options for breakfast. Employees are very nice, the place has a nice decoration, and atmosphere. I will come back next Time I'm in town for work.
Staff is amazing. They made our time there great. Food was good and the atmosphere is was fun.
Hands down the best coffee ever! My go to for food is the avocado egg wrap and it is so reasonable + great service!! Best breakfast/coffee spot in town.
WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE. I tried placing an order for pick up and the lady on the phone was extremely rude. You can sense her nasty attitude through the phone.
It was okay for the first time coffee pretty much made the meal better.
Yummy! Thanks for our frozen mocha coffees!!! Best we’ve ever had!
Made a visit to Tampa and this wonderful place made the trip amazing!! I got a simple B.L.T and was surprised at the mound of bacon that came on my sandwich!! Thank you!! Made the rest of my day lol

Ordered the gyro pita for delivery while I was at work and it was literally drenched in the sauce. Completely messy. Literally would think this is a joke. I don’t know how any cook could actually make a gyro like that and think it’s okay. My gyro was drenched and sauce was all over the paper they wrapped it in. I had to take it back wasting my entire 30 minute lunch break. If I had more than 30 minutes for my lunch I would have asked for a refund but I was hungry and just needed food. Staff is rude on the phone. Will never order from here again and would never recommend this place to anyone.
Big portion great food and service
The wait was ridiculous!  It killed my experience.  If it wasn’t for my husband, I would have l left.  But the French toast was pretty good.

Went for breakfast with my daughter not long ago since we were on this side of town. The food was excellent. I didn't catch the servers name but it was her second day on the job. I just want to tell her she did a great job.  If we're on this side if town again we will be back.

Food is good and love to support downtown business, but the staff does not wear masks properly or they wear fake mesh masks. Certainly does not make me feel safe being a patron there. Leaving five stars because I don’t want to hurt their reviews, but hope they take this feedback and take the pandemic seriously, especially being in food service.
I go to Moxies very often and love it!  Everything about this place - food, service, clean,  owners is spectacular!

French toast had to much cinnamon, over powering.  Their breakfast potatoes were just fresh french fries sliced thin and in circles.  Guess I was expecting more hash brown style.  Scrambled eggs were more milk then egg.  They forgot my toast.  Coffee was good
great coffee, great impossible vegan burger. very chill atmosphere to eat and work.

The atmosphere is nice and so was the staff but the food was extremely bland. Both omelets were bland. The Cuban toast was slightly buttered and the French toast left something to be desired. I thought the Belgian waffle had a nice texture and flavor. I'd love to give a good review because the service was great but I was very disappointed in our food

Horrible customer service over the phone. First of all the food is pricey but I wanted breakfast and I work in a store that’s in walking distance. so I called in to place an order and upon asking questions to get exactly what I wanted, I was treated extremely rude. The girl on the phone started rambling about upcharges for everything which I would have been fine with if she wasn’t talking to me the way she was. Needless to say I cancelled the order I was about to place and took my business to SAMIRIA which is right next door and they did not dissappoint!
Great ambiance & decor. The service was very sociable and kind. Feeling here is like a restaurant in Fort Worth I liked.
i really loved this place. the service was very sociable and kind. it has a nice interior.
The barista was so sweet and adorable. My coffe was great and i spiled it right after saying how good it was. She insisted on making me another one. Thanks for the good food and hospitality
normally i would have posted a pic but food looked so good i couldn't stop. i've had nothing but great experiences here and will keep coming back. prices are fair i would say.
Delicious breakfast there this morning
Good food ans service!
Great little downtown place!
Amazing services and food. I love it!
It's ok
Prices were fair for the quality of the food.
Service treated us so kindly. The prices are fair for the quality of food. Food is similar to a cafe in Portland I loved.
Missed this place, never disappoints. Great food, great service.
i was so stuffed. the service here is outstanding. the bill was decent for the quality.
the staff was sociable and attentive. this place has a good feel to it. this place has great reviews for a reason.
Super friendly I love the food 🥘
We enjoyed Mom's 75th birthday there today. Friendly, delicious and affordable.

This is a quaint little lunch place in downtown Tampa. I have only had coffee  here, however, it is very good.  This time I had 2 pumps of vanilla and a pump of pumpkin spice with non fat milk, extra hot  You can eat or drink inside or outside. Masks are required inside unless you are seated.
The bill won't shock you. This place has great reviews for a reason.
best Cuban sandwiches and mango smoothies in Tampa :’) Love the vibe and atmosphere, owners are also very friendly

My husband and I enjoyed lattes, a gorgeous croissant sandwich, and a smoothie! I love the atmosphere of this place and let me tell you! Their vanilla iced lattes are BOMB! :) Thank you for your quick service!
(Translated by Google) They treated us very well and with respect  (Original) Nos trataron muy bien y con respeto

Love this cafe! I’ve tried a few different items- salads & sandwiches have all been delicious ! My husband said it was the best Cuban sandwich he’s ever had. We will keep coming back. Excellent customer service. Friendly staff, clean tables, good food & drinks !

Fabulous find on our trek downtown in search of brunch. Service was great and the food was most delicious and savory. A plus was having a mimosa on the menu. Food was served quickly and was plenty to fill you up. Highly recommend as there were plenty of healthy menu items to choose from, too!
Great food, great atmosphere, good people working. Always fast and fresh.
Salads are great
Service was slow and when I asked for a sauce I was reminded next time there would be a charge. Only one slice of meat in the sandwich for $7
Very nice people working here. They are as cheery at 6:30 in the morning as they are at 2 in the afternoon.
Great food and friendly staff
Great atmosphere and great people that work there
Love their Cuban sandwich
Excellent food, service, and coffee. My go to lunch joint
The staff were friendly and attentive. A nice place to come back to. What a lovely experience!

They have a great atmosphere there the place is just awesome.  Jenny is amazing the girl is a very hard worker and the food is always delicious  you want find a more relax  and enjoyable  place to eat.

I live in Charlotte but every time I visit Tampa, I stop by Moxies to see Jenny and Hailey!! They are such wonderful, friendly people and the food is always amazing!!! They are fast workers and take serious pride in their work! If you’ve never been, I recommend you go!!
I absolutely love Moxies! I recommend this place to all my friends. The food is delicious and the staff is very friendly and they remember me by my name. I’ve been coming to this place for years.

Moxies is my go to spot because everyone there is so personable, my main front end lady Jenny  not only remembers my order but she picks back up on the convo we left off at. You don’t get that type of service anymore anywhere. 💗 I’ll always be a loyal customer.
Good clean place fast service even when it gets full! Staff is always nice
Good food, a little snug with the seating but overall nice place to eat.

I go to Moxies for 5 reasons : They're Fast, They're Fun, They're Friendly, The food is amazing and the woman who runs the show in the front, Jennifer - is the best.  She remembers me, my orders and is very personable.

I wanted to order a chocolate chip cookie and I asked if they were fresh out the oven. The cashier responded in a very rude and short manner: No there are from last week.... They after that she raised her voice and said: of course the cookies are fresh. What do you think? I walked out without ordering anything.  I could do without the rudeness. I am a customer after all, and I asked a very innocent question.  Very unpleasant experience
Lots of great GF and vegan options and delicious healthy smoothies. Menu is extensive! Cant wait to come back!
Staff and Service is first class and best coffee house in Tampa
Coffee was good.
Great food and amazing service!

Nice and cosy place with a lot of decent breakfast options. I had the chia seed oatmeal which was a decent portion of a delicious porridge. There's water and free wifi and the cappuccino was decent.  I may return here another day and try more options.
Food took forever to come out, bacon was thin and precooked, they didn't have the fruit for the strawberry and banana parfait, not impressed...
Sandwich good but to small for the price. If I spend good money I expect a decent portion. Service was good and quick.
Great sandwiches for the price.

I placed a online order and showed up at the suggested time. I ended up waiting about 30 minutes. When I finally got my a caprese salad there were only two tomatoes on it. I also ordered a adult grilled cheese and the sandwich was poorly put together and smashed/ sticking to the paper..... I’ve heard nothing but good things about this place so I’m not sure what happened with my order.
Great coffee and breakfast bowls
Great spot, good food and service!
Love it! So yummy!
Loved the Ice Chai Tea.
delicious, best breakfast sandwiches in Downtown Tampa
Amazing food
Decent little place. Kind staff. Good coffee.  Quaint atmosphere.  Great location.  Food was quick, hot,  and quite good.

Moxies is my favorite coffee shop I’m Downtown Tampa! The staff is friendly and hard working. The owners are innovative, clean, and organized.  Moxies breathes life into our community! Shout out to my girls at Moxies: Jenny, Kenya, Hailey, Kenyatta, and of course Karen and Bob! #MoxiesRules
Best smoothies we've ever had
Great place to chill, get away, eat some good food.
breakfast croissant came with ONE piece of bacon that was broken into 2 pieces. bread and eggs were not fresh. very disappointed
Coffee and pastries are amazing. For lunch the salads are large, filling and diverse.
Not a frequent customer, however It's always packed with business... Good coffee.

Stopped in for breakfast on my visit to down town Tampa and it was awesome!  Food was great, atmosphere was welcoming and clean!  Staff was friendly and helpful.  And I enjoyed a mimosa with breakfast.  Went back for lunch as well.  Sandwiches and salads were delicious!
A downtown staple! Great coffee!!!

Fast experience and great food selection. This is a well organized cafe.  I stopped by after landing from NYC, And I was surprised of the range of food they offer, wifi is reliable, very clean tables and Bathrooms. The staff was very friendly and helpful.  I end up coming here a few times since I found the place very cosy and reliable during my business breaks.  Moxie's handles fair prices and I wish It could be open on the afternoon too.  I'll stop by next time for fresh coffee or a small bottle of proseco.
Great sandwichesan soups salads an as for price very reasonable for what u get.
The staff was friendly and observant. Prices that won't break you.
Good food and we got our order pretty quickly! We had the Tuscana sandwich and the gyro breakfast as well as some sweet tea. I would highly recommend the tuscana sandwich!! It was really good! 💯
Great food and service
Probably the worst dining expirience in all of downtown Tampa. The owner is very rude to patrons and his staff.
Awesome Cuban bread and eggs
Cute little cafe downtown, with overall good menu for everyone’s taste. Efficient for those in a hurry for a quick bite to eat.
Nice spot to meet for coffee and a snack
The food is always really good, but the service always takes forever. Most of the time I end up going somewhere else downtown for lunch because it can take 20 minutes for a deli sandwich order!
Great breakfast at a decent price! Would definitely go back & recommend!
Pedro is the man!!
Try the fresh rolls👍
Delightful breakfast

We had two Latte, a wrap and a waffle. We paid over 30 $ for this. The taste of the Latte and waffle was good, the wrap was okay. The staff could be more friendly and we had finished our meals before the Latte came. In addition, it would be more environmentel-friendly to get real cups when sit in.
Used to be one of my favorite spots downtown...has changed a lot and the Cuban sandwich was horrible 😟

I’ve been going to this place for years very consistent food is always fresh the owners are always there very hard-working people I always get the sandwich called “the boss “ that’s my favorite but they have other ones like “the kitchen sink “or “the Sears Tower “ what I’m trying to say is you will definitely not leave their hungry and the ingredients are the best don’t hesitate to try this place while you’re in the area..
Excellent as usual...great food, great service!
Met are good friends Paul & Sue Colonna from PA. here and had breakfast with the owners and friends Bob and Karen Carr.
Excellent!!!

Are we tired of most of the national chain coffee shop. It is nice to to have a chance in brand name. This local coffee shop located at downtown that serve northern part of the downtown area. They do Catering and provide sandwich and munch. The place is trendy. I like vibrant atmosphere.  Today I am going for the mocha ice coffee. It is a bit chocolatier but have all the mojo. Good tasty coffee. Just to let all you know, caffeine never affects me. Most of the time I drink coffee is for the flavor and pleasure. They do have good flavor.
Great place to eat food.
Good chili and salads
Best sandwich place downtown. Coffee bar selection is first class. Breakfast looks good too
They were very busy when we went for lunch but we still felt taken care of and the salad was supper filling and delicious!

The atmosphere was very nice, lots of wood features with that coffee bar feel - not just a cafe with an espresso machine like other places.  Ordered a cafe con leche, extremely rich coffee (in a good way), a tad on the sweeter side for my taste, but nothing a little request later can fix.  Ordered 2 gluten free cubans (heresy for the bread, I know), they were toasted warm and still warm after I walked back to the office, but the only peevish thing was all the meat was plopped in the center of the bread instead evenly distributed. Again, peevish, but it was still very tasty.  Will be going back to try their breakfast options and other gluten free items.

Moxies has, hands down, the best coffee downtown. The food is always super fresh and the staff is incredibly friendly. If you are following the keto diet there are several options here and the staff is very knowledgeable about what you can and cant eat. The setting here is very cozy so if you dont like being up close and personal with strangers, get your java and food to go.
The place has gone downhill the past few years. The food is decent, but the service and timeliness is just too long to make this a lunch spot. It's sad, really.
It took too to get our food and it was cold . Next door restaurant has better service

So over priced for the quality of food and poor atmosphere. It’s like eating at a college cafeteria. Everyone is crammed together, walking around you, bumping into you. It definitely didn’t live up to the hype for us.

(Translated by Google) Very bad the service takes a long time and the clerk without a glove took the cookies out of the oven and touched her nose a lot, which is disgusting God  (Original) Muy mala el servicio se demora mucho y la dependiente sin guante sacaba las galletitas del horno y se tocaba mucho la nariz que asco dios
Gyro feta cheese Cuban toast with egg and provolone. Say yeah boy

A bit pricey for breakfast foods just like the next door First Watch (about $12 for a healthy turkey omelette), but the food is without a doubt five stars.  The coffee tastes great and the workers are nice as well.
Clean place, quick service and friendly staff

Delicious food! I was able to get a gluten free cuban that was amazing. The atmosphere was fun and the staff was helpful and understanding about my wife's gluten sensitivity. I would highly recommend here if you can't have gluten but need a cuban sandwich!

Had breakfast here this morning -- a breakfast burrito. The food was OK; prices were good; coffee was good; service was slow. My wife had a scrambler; her eggs and potatoes were good, but a little greasy. Not a bad choice.
Love this place for breakfast! Love everybody that works there, especially Jenny!! Such friendly staff. I go here weekly
Good food. Good house brew coffee. Cookies looked great. Seemed like they werent really ready to open yet.....was there about 06:45am....I Will go again.
Best coffe in town
The chef salad is fantastic, worth the price.  Service is a little slow but food is quality
Amazing coffee mine was a vanilla lavender latte 😁
Went to get breakfast Saturday morning. Closed. Well so much for correct business hours.

Food good, service was pretty terrible...we  watched our wraps get made and then sit on the shelf for 10 minutes as people walked by them. When I walked up and pointed it out the owner replied sir we are trying to get things out of the kitchen. She then scared the whole store by screaming across it at full volume looking for someone...not a quiet place for coffee or homework.

Such a great little cafe in downtown. They have all kinds of sandwiches and soups, not to mention one of the best peanut butter and jelly combo selections in Tampa! Oh and the coffee is great too! Also has healthy menu options
Best caramel maccchiato I have ever had!!!!!!

I've been twice for lunch for their salads.   Theres a nice independent feel to the place.  Soft rock music.  Counter service.  Mostly high chaired tables.  About $7 for a half salad. A decent value. I have only tried three of the many surrounding restaurants.
The food is always great
The food is really good management though at this place is trash

Their food is OK, nothing special. The service and cleanliness could use some improvement. We went in for breakfast and the place was practically empty, employees just relaxing, yet there were several tables covered in food crumbs. The place is not terrible, but not great, 3 stars.
Veggie omelette was tasty. Coffee slightly cold.  Staff focused on catering orders.
My husband and I decided to try Moxie's on a whim and it did not disappoint. The food was excellent, staff friendly, and comfortable atmosphere..
Good coffee, good breakfast, good service, we stop at Moxie's every time we are in Tampa.

The Coffee was good; however, without exaggeration, the worst Reuben I've ever had.  The "slab of rye" was a thin slice of cheap wheat toast (the $1 a loaf variety),  perhaps 2 thin slices of deli meat, a dab of sour kraut.  The whole sandwich was just under 1/2" thick (for perspective).  Over $8 for that sandwich, ala cart, had me dumbfounded...

This place is so hit or miss for me. Their roast beef sandwich is literally the best I've ever had! But then I had my second bad experience today where my coworkers and I ordered breakfast (scrambled eggs, potatoes, bacon) and we had it delivered. The eggs were SO overcooked they had brown parts on them and were extremely rubbery. The potatoes were under cooked and the bacon was like leather. All of it was cold. Pretty gross all around and very disappointing. I probably won't risk it anymore.
Quite cafe, staff is very kind and food is great.

Best french dip I have ever had. Moxies looks small from the outside but is roomy on the inside. Also, coffee is great and staff is friendly. I recommend to order ahead during lunchtime because they are popular!
Went on a Monday morning. Wasn't crowded. Food was good.

I used to eat at Moxie's every day when I worked in downtown Tampa. I miss the their breakfast sandwiches sooo much. Really good breakfast food and caffeinated beverages. I wish they were open on weekends but I understand that may not be a wise business choice. Great place to eat if you're in the area and they're open.
Horrible breakfast. Taste like nothing.
Love this place
Had the "healthy breakfast sandwich" and it was delicious. I'll be coming back!
Poor service
Best breakfast at a good price downtown
Good place to get sandwiches, salads, and coffee
Worst lunch ever!!
Great food, great prices, very friendly customer service. Love this family restaurant. May be my favorite place downtown!

Love their coffee and food, I have been duped by their hours a few times though. They've had many changes in when they're open over the past couple years and it's lead me to be extra cautious before making the trip downtown to be sure they're open.

The food is very good and there is a wide selection...but whenever I explicitly ask for no tomato - they still put those chunks of tomato in my wrap. It's happened 5 times in a row. Luckily I'm just grossed out by the food and not allergic to it. Lol
Great coffee, great sandwiches!  Great place for breakfast or lunch
Excellent service and food!!! Definitely check it out!!
great food.  great environment. thanks!!
Good food.

Fantastic food, my favorite here for breakfast is the lo carb scramble and lunch is the gyro pita. Also love the WiFi Waiter service that allows me to skip the line during rush lunch hours. Just connect to the WiFi and place an order from your phone, no app required!

Moxies is tops downtown Tampa, coffee, breakfast and even lunch you have to stop in.  This place with it's eclectic environment is sure to please all! The staff are exceptional,  the coffee is like none around!  Grab yourself a double shot espresso, of your favorite flavor add on an everything bagel with cream cheese,  tomatoe and bacon (my own little invention). You won't be disappointed! Tell em' Paul sent you!
One of my go-to spots downtown for lunch. Their menu is huge and there's something for everyone. Nice people and consistently good food.

Coffee is amazing, staff is friendly. Food is made to order so you can essentially concoct your own customized meal. Sometimes it gets busy at lunch but they have a free app to order for pick-up, or go to the website.

It is a great little coffee shop that also serves breakfast and lunch and has a good assortment of fresh baked goods like cinnamon rolls, muffins, and cookies. My green eggs and Ham sandwich was delicious and a couple of people that came in after me and saw mine ordered the same thing because it looked so good. Also the sandwich is huge. Coffee was great too.
Loving my smoothie & huge cup of coffee!

Staying at #AloftTampa. Asked the front desk for"mom and pop" restaurant suggestions as I like to go to them when I travel.  They recommended Moxie's; within walking distance.  Staff was personable, helpful fun and friendly!  Food was good, coffee even better.
Great food and coffee
Excellent food, with great service. Went in with our kids for breakfast and everyone was more than helpful.
Awesome place to eat the Cuban breakfast with the Cuban coffee is wonderful and they're open early and they're so friendly
Love the downtown salad!

Love my Moxies!  The coffee, sandwiches, salads... oh my!  Everything is prepared when ordered so you know its fresh.  Coffee is amazing!  Did I say amazing!  Love getting something from the espresso bar here, the barista's are always willing to help you create something special.  So many choices.
Ordered from Uber Eats, sandwich came soggy and wrapped up with a dirty glove. Are you kidding me guys? Not that I would ever eat here again but damn that's gross! #dobetter
I have been here for my delicious Moxies Mocha on my way to work as well going back for either breakfast or lunch.  Food is very fresh and prepared the way that you like it.  Staff is very friendly.

Great, locally owned, coffee shop in downtown Tampa. The staff greets you by name and takes every care in making you the best cup of coffee - ever. Try their ECH - Egg Cheese and Ham pressed breakfast Cuban. It is delicious. If you are still hungry there's lots of hand made desserts to choose from.

Never really hit Moxie's up before as there are too many great options downtown and we've been deterred by their "Where's Waldo-like" mascot branding. We decided to get a couple of Italian sandwiches, and we were delighted to see that the meat was actually Italian-quality meat... like in th sandwiches you get up north, not the substitute mystery meat blends you get on most Italian sandwiches. However, correct me if I am wrong, I believe that you are supposed to remove the stems from the pepperoncinis before you hide them on the sandwiches you are serving. Pretty unpleasant surprise to get a stem jammed in your gums after that first bite.

3 stars for food, ordered a Cuban and the wife got a roast beef sandwich, got there just before noon and ordered, had to ask for food to go at 12:40pm as it still wasn't out, so I wasn't late getting back to work. But on a good note the food was good as we ate in the car on the way.

It was extremely homey and I felt welcome right away with the rest of my party of 3. Delicous food and great options of exactly what people want!! Love this place and so glad I had breakfast here. Kinda makes me sad I live in MN and not right here in tampa. Also, the people who work here are very kind and are not afraid to tell jokes and talk. Lots of great conversation! Thank you Moxies!

This is my first time eating Moxie's. (I got my food to go.)  The place seemed pretty nice and welcoming inside though, so maybe I'll eat in next time.  I got the "Say Cheese" sandwich with potato salad on the side.  Both were excellent.  It's not inexpensive, but that seems to be the norm for lunch downtown.  Plus, the sandwich was pretty big.  The girl who helped me was courteous and friendly.
Not dog friendly at all... Just go to first watch they allow service dog
Bad customer service.  They would not listen to our coffee request. Menus are hard to read because they move on the screen. Potatoes tasted like cardboard. Eggs were overcooked.
1st time here..  Staff was very pleasant, coffee was delicious and the Nova Lox on an everything Bengal was on point. Great place my husband and I will be back. 😀
Friendly staff, great espresso drinks and lunch items.
Willing to let us eat late, fun personalitys. Very clean and fresh feel to this place!!!!!!
